cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.AR 

The paper discusses the implementation of a framework for live service migration in mobile edge clouds, which involves network infrastructure, distributed computing, and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with cloud computing and data centers, which fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The framework involves layering and encapsulation, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the implementation of the framework using readily available technologies, which is related to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of real applications, which is related to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
